TY  - JOUR
AU  - Gu, Chao
AU  - Mattesini, Fabrizio
AU  - Monnet, Cyril
AU  - Wright, Randall
T1  - Banking: A New Monetarist Approach
PY  - 2013
Y1  - 2013/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rds037
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 80
IS  - 2
SP  - 636
EP  - 662
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We develop a model where: (i) banks take deposits and make investments; (ii) their liabilities facilitate third-party transactions. Other models have (i) or (ii), not both, although we argue they are intimately connected: we show that they both emerge from limited commitment. We describe an environment, characterize desirable allocations, and interpret the outcomes as banking arrangements. Banks are essential: without them, the set of feasible allocations is inferior. As a technical contribution, we characterize dynamically optimal credit allocations with frictions, show they involve backloading, and analyse how this interacts with banking. We also confront the theory with economic history.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rds037
ER  - 



